Source: riscv-tools
Maintainer: Darius Rad <darius@bluespec.com>
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Standards-Version: 3.9.8
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), autoconf, automake, autotools-dev, curl, libmpc-dev, libmpfr-dev, libgmp-dev, gawk, build-essential, bison, flex, texinfo, gperf, libtool, patchutils, bc, zlib1g-dev, python-dev, pkg-config
#Homepage: http://www.bluespec.com/

Package: riscv32-unknown-elf-rv32im
Architecture: any
Section: devel
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
#Suggests:
Conflicts: openocd
Description: Tools for the riscv32-unknown-elf target, rv32im variant
 This package contains development tools for RISC-V.  This package
 contains the riscv32-unknown-elf toolchain, targeting bare metal
 application with the Newlib C library.
 .
 The hardware targeted by these tools is version 2.1 of the User Level
 ISA, variant RV32IM.  In addition, the Privileged Architecture
 version 1.10 is supported.

